Oops, sorry you stepped into this. In addition to what Linda Jo said, it might help to consider that any poll of this comments section would produce a biased result--it would not be a democratic representation of the puzzle solving public. The people who respond here are a tiny, tiny fraction of the Sunday puzzle solvers: those who solve online, in the print paper, and in the published collections. (It looks as though Will Shortz is up to Volume 13 and there are other collections as well.)

A number of people who subscribed over the last couple of years have been advocating in these comments that the Times make the puzzles simpler so that they can do them without the traditional learning curve. Tempers from long-time devotees have gotten a wee bit frayed.

